To construct the intersection poset \( L(\mathcal{A}) \) for an arrangement of \( N \) families \( \mathcal{A}_i \) of \( D \) parallel hyperplanes in general position, we use a Hasse diagram. The poset is ranked by codimension, with the ambient space at the top, hyperplanes from each family at the next level, and their intersections at the bottom. Hyperplanes in the same family are parallel and do not intersect, so they appear as incomparable siblings.

```latex
\documentclass{standalone}
\usepackage{tikz}
\usetikzlibrary{positioning,arrows.meta}

\begin{document}
\begin{tikzpicture}[
    node distance=1.2cm and 0.8cm,
    hasse/.style={circle, draw, minimum size=0.8cm, inner sep=0},
    label/.style={font=\small},
    edge/.style={-{Stealth[length=2mm]}, shorten >=1pt, shorten <=1pt}
]

% Top element (ambient space)
\node[hasse] (top) at (0, 3) {};
\node[label, above=0.2cm of top] {$\text{Codim } 0$};

% Level 1: Hyperplanes from N families
\foreach \i in {1,2,3} {
    \node[hasse] (h\i) at (3*\i-6, 1.5) {};
    \node[label, below=0.2cm of h\i] {$\mathcal{A}_{\i}$};
}
\node[label, above=0.2cm of h2] {$\text{Codim } 1$};

% Level 2: Intersections of hyperplanes
\foreach \i in {1,2,3} {
    \foreach \j in {\i,...,3} {
        \ifnum \i < \j
            \node[hasse] (i\i\j) at (3*(\i+\j)/2 - 6, 0) {};
            \node[label, below=0.2cm of i\i\j] {$\mathcal{A}_{\i} \cap \mathcal{A}_{\j}$};
            \draw[edge] (h\i) -- (i\i\j);
            \draw[edge] (h\j) -- (i\i\j);
        \fi
    }
}
\node[label, above=0.2cm of i12] {$\text{Codim } 2$};

% Connect top to hyperplanes
\foreach \i in {1,2,3} {
    \draw[edge] (top) -- (h\i);
}

% Legend
\node[hasse, label=below:Hyperplane] at (4, 1.5) {};
\node[hasse, fill=black!10, label=below:Intersection] at (4, 0) {};

\end{tikzpicture}
\end{document}
```

**Key Features:**
1. **Poset Structure**: Three codimension levels (0, 1, 2) representing the ambient space, hyperplanes, and their intersections.
2. **Parallel Families**: Hyperplanes in the same family (e.g., \( \mathcal{A}_1 \)) are incomparable siblings.
3. **General Position**: All intersections between different families are distinct and non-empty.
4. **Visual Clarity**: 
   - Circular nodes for poset elements.
   - Vertical/horizontal positioning for hierarchical clarity.
   - Arrows indicating covering relations.
   - Legend for element types.

Adjust `N=3` in the loop to match the number of families, and modify coordinates in the `foreach` loops for different hyperplane counts \( D \).

